'''Nimiaghat''' is a railway station on the  [[Asansol-Gaya section]] of [[Grand Chord]]. It is located in [[Giridih district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Jharkhand]].  It is located at the base of [[Shikharji]] (Parashnath Hill) and is on one of the routes for climbing the hill

==History==
The [[Grand Chord]] was opened in 1906.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-history3.html | title = IR History <U+2013> Part III (1900-1947)| publisher = IRFCA | accessdate = 23 April 2013 }}</ref>

==Electrification==
The Gomoh-Koderma sector was electrified in 1961-62.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://irfca.org/docs/electrification-history.html|title = History of Electrification| publisher= IRFCA| accessdate = 20 Apri 2013}}</ref>

